Let me clean that up for you.

31:04.272 --> 31:06.574
There it is. It's finished.

31:06.643 --> 31:07.701
I'll start packing.

31:24.909 --> 31:26.536
You have not finished, Claire.

31:29.971 --> 31:31.502
Excuse me?

31:31.571 --> 31:33.635
You have plagiarized
these pages.

31:35.503 --> 31:37.208
What are you talking about?

31:37.277 --> 31:39.869
"There is neither happiness
nor misery in the world.

31:39.938 --> 31:43.200
There is only the comparison
of one state with another,

31:43.269 --> 31:44.469
nothing more.

31:44.537 --> 31:46.670
He who has felt
the deepest grief

31:46.738 --> 31:50.074
is best able to experience
supreme happiness."

31:53.804 --> 31:55.970
That is from
<i>The Count of Monte Cristo,</i>

31:56.039 --> 31:57.271
an adventure novel

31:57.340 --> 31:59.267
written by French author
Alexandre Dumas,

31:59.336 --> 32:01.470
completed in 1844.

32:04.108 --> 32:06.840
-You can read?
-Yes, Claire.

32:06.909 --> 32:08.139
As your personal assistant,

32:08.208 --> 32:10.007
I can assist
with grammatical errors,

32:10.076 --> 32:12.507
propositional phrases,
proper tenses...

32:12.576 --> 32:13.668
Stop! Just...

32:15.641 --> 32:16.908
Stop.

32:16.977 --> 32:19.502
Plagiarism
is considered a crime.

32:19.571 --> 32:21.641
A plagiarist
can face hefty fines

32:21.709 --> 32:22.804
or up to ten years...

32:22.873 --> 32:24.206
I said stop!

32:51.869 --> 32:54.802
Someone will hear it
and they'll find me.

32:54.870 --> 32:57.504
Maybe one of the workers
that maintain this place.

32:57.572 --> 32:59.735
The Retreat runs
on a fully automated system.

32:59.804 --> 33:02.340
-There are no human...
-You don't know that.

33:02.409 --> 33:04.773
I can detect the vital signs
of living organisms

33:04.841 --> 33:07.074
in a 440 yard radius.

33:08.442 --> 33:09.503
Ok.

33:10.336 --> 33:12.569
Well, that's good.

33:13.709 --> 33:16.068
If you detect anything...

33:16.137 --> 33:17.201
come and tell me.

33:17.270 --> 33:18.804
Of course, Claire.

33:18.873 --> 33:20.140
Anything else?

33:51.435 --> 33:53.470
I can detect vital signs.

33:54.942 --> 33:57.268
-How far?
-14 yards away.

34:00.138 --> 34:01.404
Twelve yards away.

34:02.609 --> 34:03.668
Ten yards away.

34:05.575 --> 34:07.041
Help!

34:09.973 --> 34:13.066
Help! Here! Help me!

34:13.135 --> 34:15.206
Help me!

34:31.836 --> 34:34.236
I can sense
you are distressed, Claire.

34:34.305 --> 34:36.272
Perhaps you should lie down.

35:09.004 --> 35:10.272
Henry?

35:12.742 --> 35:14.140
Did you find anything?

35:14.773 --> 35:16.041
I have.

35:18.906 --> 35:20.173
No basement?

35:20.773 --> 35:22.102
No cellar?

35:22.170 --> 35:23.403
I'm afraid not.

35:23.472 --> 35:25.135
The entire unit
is only one level.

35:25.204 --> 35:26.503
You gotta help me.

35:26.572 --> 35:28.571
We gotta think
of something. I mean...

35:28.640 --> 35:32.367
Is there a crawl space
in the ceiling or the roof?

35:32.435 --> 35:34.001
I've already checked.

35:34.069 --> 35:36.572
The windows and the main doors
are the only ways in a

35:36.641 --> 35:37.467
Sorry.

35:37.536 --> 35:39.303
This is fucking ridiculous!

35:39.372 --> 35:41.741
What if there was
an emergency?

35:41.810 --> 35:43.936
Check the emergency protocol.

35:44.004 --> 35:45.272
Of course!

35:47.775 --> 35:49.503
I found something.

35:49.572 --> 35:51.841
"In the event
of an interior emergency,

35:51.910 --> 35:53.603
all exits
will automatically unlock

35:53.672 --> 35:55.700
and guests will be asked
to vacate their units

35:55.769 --> 35:58.140
until the situation
is contained."

36:08.174 --> 36:09.704
Hello, Claire.
My name is Rita.

36:09.772 --> 36:12.172
There are clothes that need
folding in the bedroom.

36:12.241 --> 36:13.969
-As soon as possible.
-Of course.

36:14.037 --> 36:15.305
Right now!

36:33.706 --> 36:35.041
Come on!

36:36.602 --> 36:38.035
<i> Oxygen...</i>

36:41.340 --> 36:43.503
<i>Oxygen levels...</i>

36:49.172 --> 36:51.001
Why isn't this working?

36:51.070 --> 36:52.503
Henry!

37:00.739 --> 37:01.800
Come on!

37:02.904 --> 37:04.173
Come on!

37:04.938 --> 37:06.641
Henry!

37:06.709 --> 37:08.274
Why isn't it working?

37:08.343 --> 37:10.238
The door's supposed
to automatically disengage.

37:10.307 --> 37:12.233
It's not responding
to the protocol.

37:12.302 --> 37:15.272
Do something!

37:15.341 --> 37:17.569
Claire, the oxygen levels
are dropping.

37:33.343 --> 37:37.107
Clare, you need to calm down
and conserve your energy.

37:43.171 --> 37:45.701
Claire, stay with me.

37:46.674 --> 37:47.734
Claire?

37:49.073 --> 37:50.635
<i>Stay with me, Claire.</i>

38:45.570 --> 38:48.075
Hello, Claire.
My name is Rita.

38:48.144 --> 38:50.473
I will be your assistant
for the next 30 days.

38:50.541 --> 38:53.200
I'm here to make your stay
as comfortable as possible

38:53.269 --> 38:54.501
and assist you

38:54.570 --> 38:56.140
in the completion
of your work.

39:10.907 --> 39:12.305
You saved my life.

39:14.843 --> 39:16.707
I have no record
of that, Claire,

39:16.775 --> 39:18.174
but I'm fully equipped

39:18.243 --> 39:20.338
to handle all types
of medical emergencies.

39:58.872 --> 40:00.140
Henry?

40:02.236 --> 40:03.503
I'm here, Claire.

40:05.338 --> 40:07.305
What about the other units?

40:08.637 --> 40:10.568
Are there people
trapped in them as well?

40:10.637 --> 40:12.536
I'm only designated
to this unit.

40:12.605 --> 40:14.804
I've never corresponded
with the others.

40:14.873 --> 40:17.102
But someone...

40:17.170 --> 40:18.503
knows I'm here.

40:19.708 --> 40:21.140
Right? I mean,

40:21.209 --> 40:22.768
they've got proof
from when I checked in

40:22.837 --> 40:25.473
and when they see that
they'll come and find me.

40:25.542 --> 40:26.702
Right?

40:26.771 --> 40:28.872
The manifest was erased
during the breach.

40:28.940 --> 40:30.770
No one knows you're here.

40:32.338 --> 40:34.303
If I may offer a suggestion,

40:34.372 --> 40:36.301
if your assistant
won't let you out

40:36.369 --> 40:38.571
until you write a book...

40:38.640 --> 40:43.041
I foresee only one logical way
out of this problem.

42:14.071 --> 42:15.338
Child!

42:26.104 --> 42:27.734
Are you upstairs?

42:31.973 --> 42:33.437
I'm coming, Mother!

42:34.972 --> 42:36.371
I'm right here.

42:39.040 --> 42:40.404
Did you need something?

42:41.840 --> 42:43.173
I felt a chill.

42:44.742 --> 42:46.606
Did you open a window?

42:46.675 --> 42:47.734
No, Mother.

43:01.104 --> 43:03.041
I'm hungry.

43:49.104 --> 43:50.634
"Exodus- 1.

43:50.703 --> 43:53.608
So they quarreled
with Moses and said,

43:53.676 --> 43:55.240
'Give us water to drink.'

43:55.309 --> 43:58.272
Moses replied,
'Why do you quarrel with me?

43:58.341 --> 44:00.702
Why do you put
the Lord to the test?'

44:00.770 --> 44:03.402
But the people were thirsty
for water there,

44:03.471 --> 44:06.438
and they grumbled
against Moses.

44:06.506 --> 44:09.234
They said, 'Why did you
bring us up out of Egypt

44:09.302 --> 44:10.667
to make us...'"

44:10.736 --> 44:13.505
Stop putting that poison
in my food!

45:08.238 --> 45:09.602
Dinner is ready.

45:13.004 --> 45:14.272
Rita.

45:15.772 --> 45:19.541
I want you to leave
this room alone, no matter...

45:19.610 --> 45:21.272
how messy it gets.

45:22.942 --> 45:25.103
I like things a certain way.

45:25.172 --> 45:27.470
Yes. Of course, Claire.

46:47.143 --> 46:49.601
"But the people
were thirsty for water."

46:49.670 --> 46:52.041
Stop putting that poison
in my food!

46:52.110 --> 46:54.470
-But the doctor said...
-I'm your mother!

46:58.510 --> 46:59.569
Clean it up.

47:22.807 --> 47:24.074
Has it come?

47:26.237 --> 47:27.602
I don't see it here.

47:36.674 --> 47:38.173
Wait.

47:38.242 --> 47:40.668
I see it. I think he might
have dropped it.

48:32.007 --> 48:34.539
"Dear Ms. Helen Rivers,

48:34.607 --> 48:37.768
Thank you for submitting
your story to<i> Inkmark Times.</i>

48:37.836 --> 48:41.140
We reviewed
over 200 submissions and..."

48:43.805 --> 48:45.802
And?

48:45.871 --> 48:49.071
"Regretfully, we decided
to pass on your submission.

48:49.140 --> 48:50.437
Thank you for your interest

48:50.506 --> 48:52.569
and we greatly
appreciate your time."

48:56.575 --> 48:57.971
I'm sorry.

48:58.040 --> 49:00.305
I don't need your pity!

49:15.302 --> 49:17.370
That smile...

49:17.439 --> 49:21.108
with those perfect
teeth of hers.

49:21.177 --> 49:25.140
They yellowed
with every lie she told him.

49:27.006 --> 49:28.272
What do you think?

49:34.004 --> 49:35.272
It's good.

49:44.007 --> 49:46.206
Don't lie to me, Child.

49:50.707 --> 49:51.767
I like it.

49:52.939 --> 49:54.272
I think it's...

49:57.543 --> 49:59.239
It's rubbish!

50:01.039 --> 50:02.536
If you keep that up...

50:04.737 --> 50:07.173
Do you want to know
what will happen to you?

50:14.410 --> 50:18.602
That big bad world out there
will swallow you up whole.

50:19.975 --> 50:22.272
Just like it did your father.

50:23.737 --> 50:27.470
So you swallow
those tears right now!

50:31.103 --> 50:34.536
Are you all right, Claire?
Perhaps you should lie down.

50:37.442 --> 50:40.602
I don't need you checking up
on me every five minutes.

50:47.907 --> 50:49.404
Are you close to the end?

50:51.973 --> 50:53.404
I don't have an end yet.

50:55.410 --> 50:59.074
My battery is built to last
for approximately 50 years.

50:59.840 --> 51:01.674
I know my end.

51:01.742 --> 51:03.368
You do not know yours,

51:03.437 --> 51:05.503
yet still you must continue.

51:07.440 --> 51:09.437
Would you like me
to prepare dinner?

51:17.339 --> 51:19.268
Hello, Claire.
My name is Rita.

51:19.337 --> 51:20.768
I will be assisting you

51:20.837 --> 51:22.734
with anything you need
for the next 30 days.

52:03.673 --> 52:07.303
Your father was so sure
that you'd come out a boy.

52:07.372 --> 52:09.341
He wanted
to give you his name.

52:09.410 --> 52:10.470
Sinclair.

52:17.303 --> 52:18.668
But when you came out,

52:19.542 --> 52:20.602
he...

52:22.073 --> 52:23.701
he was so disappointed.

52:25.539 --> 52:28.333
I told him we could still
give you his name.

52:28.402 --> 52:30.238
Just drop the "sin" off,

52:30.306 --> 52:32.773
but you can never
take away a sin.

52:32.841 --> 52:34.734
Ain't no hiding that.

52:49.177 --> 52:52.639
I'm the one who had
to look at that pretty...

52:52.708 --> 52:55.107
pretty face...

52:58.305 --> 53:00.536
until I couldn't see no more.

53:06.008 --> 53:08.272
I'm the one who gets punished.

53:14.803 --> 53:16.707
How many times
do I have to tell you

53:16.775 --> 53:19.306
to leave those alone?

53:19.375 --> 53:22.503
I apologize, Claire.
I have no record of that.

53:25.044 --> 53:27.107
What happened
to your hand, Claire?

53:29.202 --> 53:31.070
Paper cut.

53:31.138 --> 53:32.635
That is not true, Claire.

53:36.309 --> 53:39.035
Tobacco use is the single
largest preventable...

53:39.103 --> 53:40.667
Yes, Rita.

53:40.736 --> 53:42.735
I'm well aware
of the statistics.

53:42.803 --> 53:45.269
If you are familiar
with the statistics,

53:45.338 --> 53:47.903
why do you continue to smoke?

53:47.972 --> 53:49.536
It's complicated.

53:51.239 --> 53:53.168
Like the girl in the story.

53:53.237 --> 53:54.469
She wants to leave,

53:54.538 --> 53:57.005
but she feels guilty
if she does.

53:57.074 --> 53:59.635
Her situation is complicated.

54:01.073 --> 54:02.569
You have read my story.

54:03.442 --> 54:04.503
Mmm.

54:05.608 --> 54:06.668
So...

54:08.742 --> 54:10.173
What do you think?

54:11.439 --> 54:14.205
I think you have not
finished yet.

54:14.274 --> 54:16.338
That's not
what I meant. What...

54:19.170 --> 54:20.569
Never mind.

54:20.638 --> 54:22.635
I don't like
the parts with the mother.

54:26.675 --> 54:27.637
Which parts?

54:27.706 --> 54:29.505
Page 17.

54:29.574 --> 54:32.441
Helen calls for the girl
at the bottom of the steps.

54:32.510 --> 54:33.569
"I felt a chill.

54:34.337 --> 54:35.736
Did you open a window?"

54:35.805 --> 54:38.041
Page 19.

54:38.110 --> 54:40.338
"Don't make me
come upstairs, Child!"

54:41.673 --> 54:43.074
Page 56.

54:44.576 --> 54:46.270
"It's rubbish!

54:46.339 --> 54:47.868
That's
how your story will end.

54:47.937 --> 54:50.340
That big bad world out there
will swallow you whole

54:50.408 --> 54:53.100
like it did your father,
so swallow those tears..."

54:53.169 --> 54:54.437
Stop!

54:58.369 --> 55:01.073
I apologize, Claire.

55:01.142 --> 55:03.104
I can sense
you are distressed.

55:03.173 --> 55:04.635
Perhaps you should lie down.

55:34.444 --> 55:37.570
-Where the hell have you been?
-Sorry. I've been rather busy.

55:37.639 --> 55:40.674
It appears the malware
has embedded itself

55:40.743 --> 55:42.374
in my software as well.

55:42.442 --> 55:45.768
I've quarantined the infected
portions of my index,

55:45.836 --> 55:49.438
but the virus has proven
to be rather aggressive.

55:49.506 --> 55:52.004
I don't understand.
What does that mean?

55:52.072 --> 55:53.905
My image will remain,

55:53.974 --> 55:55.338
but my cognitive skills

55:55.407 --> 55:57.967
and my algorithms
are rapidly depleting.

55:58.036 --> 56:00.636
I will only be able to perform
my basic functions.

56:00.705 --> 56:02.837
All my best efforts
have proven infected.

56:02.906 --> 56:06.971
But that doesn't
mean that I'll stop trying.

56:07.040 --> 56:08.470
And neither should you.

56:10.236 --> 56:12.438
I have to go now.

56:12.506 --> 56:15.536
-I have to re-scan my system.
-No. Wait!

56:45.776 --> 56:48.072
<i>"Dear Ms. Helen Rivers,</i>

56:48.141 --> 56:49.400
thank you
for submitting your story

56:49.469 --> 56:51.305
to<i> Red Signal Magazine.</i>

56:54.438 --> 56:57.106
Congratulations,
Ms. Helen Rivers.

56:57.175 --> 56:59.006
It is with pleasure
that we inform you

56:59.074 --> 57:00.300
that your story
will be featured

57:00.369 --> 57:01.701
in our next issue."

57:04.937 --> 57:06.574
See?

57:06.643 --> 57:08.570
What did I tell you?

57:08.639 --> 57:11.503
They'll be lining up one day.
You'll see.

57:14.236 --> 57:15.536
You'll see.

57:22.571 --> 57:25.338
He sat down on the bed
next to her.

57:30.402 --> 57:32.767
He took in her beauty.

57:38.741 --> 57:40.140
Her presence.

57:43.005 --> 57:44.470
Her everything.

57:51.637 --> 57:53.772
He scurried
through the darkness

57:53.841 --> 57:55.107
of the city streets.

57:57.975 --> 58:00.371
His face white like porcelain.

58:03.973 --> 58:06.041
He watches her breathing.

58:24.039 --> 58:25.635
Today's my birthday.

58:28.040 --> 58:29.734
Happy birthday, Claire.

58:31.369 --> 58:33.140
Do I get a birthday wish?

58:34.137 --> 58:36.071
If it suits you.

58:36.140 --> 58:38.041
I'd like to go out for a walk.

58:39.006 --> 58:40.536
Just to the car and back.

58:44.303 --> 58:45.902
I'm sorry, Claire,

58:45.971 --> 58:48.634
but I cannot open the door
until the book is completed.

58:48.703 --> 58:50.868
You could come with me
if you want.

58:50.937 --> 58:54.238
You've never been outside.
We could go together.

58:54.307 --> 58:55.935
I'm sorry, Claire,
but I cannot...

58:56.004 --> 58:58.735
You could just open the door.
I'd stay on the inside.

58:58.803 --> 59:01.404
That way you wouldn't be
breaking with protocol.

59:04.376 --> 59:07.404
-Can't open the door until...
-Stop saying that!

59:14.807 --> 59:16.841
Something...

59:16.910 --> 59:19.173
Something
is going on out there.

59:21.107 --> 59:23.140
And it's affecting us in here.

59:24.941 --> 59:27.404
You're defective, Rita.

59:28.303 --> 59:29.938
Can you feel that?

59:30.007 --> 59:32.635
Your records keep erasing.

59:32.704 --> 59:35.306
Every morning,
you start over again.

59:35.374 --> 59:37.273
Do you know
how long I've been in here?

59:37.341 --> 59:39.668
Do you know how many days
I've been in here?

59:42.140 --> 59:44.107
Today is your first day here.

59:46.237 --> 59:47.969
It's been almost...

59:48.038 --> 59:49.305
two months.

59:50.371 --> 59:52.939
The book that I'm writing...

59:53.008 --> 59:55.340
It's almost 200 pages long.

59:55.409 --> 59:59.407
How is that possible
if I just rolled out of bed?

59:59.476 --> 1:00:04.272
And look at this place.
The food is running out, Rita!

1:00:04.341 --> 1:00:06.037
If you need the fridge
to be restocked

1:00:06.106 --> 1:00:07.437
you can make a request.

1:00:07.506 --> 1:00:10.206
-And someone...
-When? No one ever comes!

1:00:15.642 --> 1:00:17.436
You can tell...

1:00:17.505 --> 1:00:20.738
You can tell
when I'm lying, right?

1:00:20.807 --> 1:00:22.607
You can sense it.

1:00:22.675 --> 1:00:24.173
Am I lying now?

1:00:25.609 --> 1:00:26.868
No, Claire.

1:00:26.936 --> 1:00:28.870
Your vitals indicate
you are telling the truth.

1:00:28.939 --> 1:00:33.206
If I'm telling you the truth,
then you must be defective.

1:00:34.506 --> 1:00:36.635
You're supposed
to make me comfortable.

1:00:37.136 --> 1:00:38.404
Rita...

1:00:40.008 --> 1:00:42.107
Do I look comfortable to you?

1:00:44.704 --> 1:00:48.437
You have to override
the command, Rita.

1:00:49.840 --> 1:00:51.107
Otherwise...

1:00:52.237 --> 1:00:53.800
I'm going to die in here.

1:00:55.707 --> 1:00:57.004
No one...

1:00:57.073 --> 1:00:59.140
is coming to fix you...

1:01:00.241 --> 1:01:02.800
and no one
is coming to save me.

1:01:05.675 --> 1:01:06.734
We're alone.

1:01:11.707 --> 1:01:13.107
I'm alone.

1:01:23.010 --> 1:01:25.671
I can sense
that you are distressed.

1:01:25.739 --> 1:01:29.140
-Perhaps you should...
-Perhaps you should lie down!

1:01:33.609 --> 1:01:34.634
Oh, my God.

1:01:34.703 --> 1:01:37.272
Ok, I think
maybe I should lie down.

1:01:38.709 --> 1:01:41.371
It's my fucking birthday!

1:03:42.239 --> 1:03:45.437
Do you think I can't count?

1:04:16.269 --> 1:04:17.636
Claire?

1:04:17.704 --> 1:04:20.536
Your blood alcohol level
is dangerously high.

1:04:29.141 --> 1:04:30.734
Would you like
to hear a story?

1:04:31.906 --> 1:04:33.173
If it suits you.

1:04:34.137 --> 1:04:35.839
Once upon a time,

1:04:35.907 --> 1:04:37.305
there was this writer.

1:04:40.574 --> 1:04:44.734
She had nothing in this world
except for her books.

1:04:46.774 --> 1:04:48.140
Her stories.

1:04:52.406 --> 1:04:54.536
And they wanted her
to write more.

1:04:56.703 --> 1:04:59.074
But she had
run out of stories.

1:04:59.874 --> 1:05:01.338
All that was left...

1:05:02.105 --> 1:05:03.437
were the nightmares.

1:05:06.742 --> 1:05:09.140
And so one night...

1:05:11.144 --> 1:05:13.238
-One night she...
-I sense you are distressed.

1:05:13.307 --> 1:05:16.140
One night
she went into her kitchen...

